description:
&lt;p&gt;This role has been developed to support the Coventry, Rugby and North Warwickshire CCG’s to proactivelysupport the implementation of the Primary Care GP IT Strategy, GP Forward View, NHS Long Term Plan and Primary Care Networks (PCN) as part of an integrated Primary Care Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Coventry and Rugby CCG is a membership organisation, representing all 66 GP practices in the area. A governing body answerable to the member practices led by elected local GPs, other clinicians and lay members supported by senior healthcare managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Warwickshire North Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG)comprises of 25 GP practices andhas beenauthorised by the NHS Commissioning Board to operate as astatutory organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic person who is able to work, learn and actively contribute within a team environment. The ideal candidate will support the Head of Primary Care Commissioning to deliver the primary care agenda for Warwickshire North and Rugby and have a specific focus on delivering the technology and digital agenda, must have excellent communication skills, a good approach in dealing with enquiries and resolving technology problems for our partners. You must have a methodical, yet flexible project management approach to system delivery and be able to exercise responsible business judgement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will have excellent leadership skills, with the ability to develop strong stakeholder relationships but also someone who has experience of working in a highly pressurised and political environment. It is desirable that the successful candidate has some awareness/knowledge of Primary Care as they will work closely with GPs and PCNs,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with experience in delivering fast paced, high pressured technology programs at scale, and who is passionate about supporting our partners so they can continue to deliver excellent care to our local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about this role, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roma Holland&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roma.holland@coventryrugbyccg.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;07818 577 917&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
